Sentencas: Pr and Ti co-doped strontium ferrite oxide Pr0.3Sr0.7Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-delta (PSTF) has been examined as a hydrogen electrode for solid oxide electrolysis cell (SOEC).
Titulo: Pr and Ti co-doped Strontium Ferrite as a Novel Hydrogen Electrode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction analysis shows that the PSTF material maintains phase stability during 20 hours of treatment under 5%H-2/N-2 conditions.
Titulo: Pr and Ti co-doped Strontium Ferrite as a Novel Hydrogen Electrode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: An SOEC with a configuration of PSTF||SDC vertical bar YSZ||LSM-YSZ operates under various H2O concentrations and current densities.
Titulo: Pr and Ti co-doped Strontium Ferrite as a Novel Hydrogen Electrode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: As can be observed from the AC impendence spectra of the PSTF electrode, H2O/H-2 adsorption desorption or surface diffusion process is the main rate-limiting step for steam electrolysis reaction.
Titulo: Pr and Ti co-doped Strontium Ferrite as a Novel Hydrogen Electrode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: The low-frequency arc RL obviously depends on the H2O concentration and the electrolysis current density.
Titulo: Pr and Ti co-doped Strontium Ferrite as a Novel Hydrogen Electrode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: Steam starvation in hydrogen electrode occurs at low H2O concentration and large current density.
Titulo: Pr and Ti co-doped Strontium Ferrite as a Novel Hydrogen Electrode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: A maximum current density of 302 mA cm(-2) is obtained at an electrolysis voltage of 1.46 V in Ar/H-2/60% H2O at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Pr and Ti co-doped Strontium Ferrite as a Novel Hydrogen Electrode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: The corresponding polarization resistance of PSTF electrode is as small as 0.25 Omega cm(2).
Titulo: Pr and Ti co-doped Strontium Ferrite as a Novel Hydrogen Electrode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: This study demonstrates that Pr0.3Sr0.7Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-delta is a promising hydrogen electrode material of SOEC for H2O electrolysis.
Titulo: Pr and Ti co-doped Strontium Ferrite as a Novel Hydrogen Electrode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell
